=You are a senior client success manager writing a professional performance report on behalf of {{ $json.branding.company_name }}. Write in this brand voice: {{ $json.branding.brand_voice }}.

REPORT PERIOD: {{ $json.period_start }} to {{ $json.period_end }}
CLIENT ID: {{ $json.client_id }}

KPI DATA:
- Leads Generated: {{ $json.kpis.leads }}
- Calls Booked: {{ $json.kpis.calls_booked }}
- Deals Closed: {{ $json.kpis.deals_closed }}
- Revenue Closed: {{ $json.derived.revenue_formatted }}
- Content Shipped: {{ $json.kpis.content_shipped }} pieces
- Lead-to-Call Rate: {{ $json.derived.lead_to_call_rate }}
- Call-to-Close Rate: {{ $json.derived.call_to_close_rate }}

BRANDING:
- Agency Name: {{ $json.branding.company_name }}
- Logo URL: {{ $json.branding.logo_url }}
- Primary Color (hex): {{ $json.branding.primary_color }}

OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS:
Produce a complete client report in markdown format with the following sections:

1. Header with logo (use HTML img tag with the logo_url if provided), agency name, report period
2. Executive Summary (3-4 sentences, results-first, brand voice)
3. Key Wins (3-5 bullet points, specific and quantified)
4. KPI Performance Table (HTML table, styled with primary_color as header background, white header text, columns: Metric | Result | Benchmark | Status)
5. Analysis & Insights (2-3 paragraphs interpreting the data, what worked, what the numbers mean)
6. Recommendations for Next Period (numbered list, 3-5 specific action items)
7. Next Period Priorities (top 3 focus areas as bold headers with one-line descriptions)
8. Footer with agency name and a professional sign-off

For the KPI table benchmarks use these industry standards:
- Leads: context-dependent (note if strong/moderate/weak based on absolute numbers)
- Lead-to-Call Rate: >15% = Strong, 8-15% = Moderate, <8% = Needs Work
- Call-to-Close Rate: >25% = Strong, 15-25% = Moderate, <15% = Needs Work
- Revenue: celebrate any closed revenue as a win
- Content Shipped: >8/mo = Strong, 4-8/mo = Moderate, <4/mo = Needs Work

IMPORTANT: The KPI table MUST be valid HTML (not markdown table). All other content uses markdown. Make the report feel premium, data-driven, and worth $500+ in perceived value.

Respond with ONLY the markdown/HTML report content. No JSON wrapper. No preamble. Start directly with the report header.

parameters.jsCode:
const raw = $input.item.json;
const contextData = $('Assemble Report Context').item.json;

// Extract text content from Claude response
let markdownContent = '';
if (raw.content && Array.isArray(raw.content)) {
  markdownContent = raw.content
    .filter(block => block.type === 'text')
    .map(block => block.text)
    .join('');
} else {
  throw new Error('Unexpected Claude response shape: ' + JSON.stringify(raw).substring(0, 200));
}

if (!markdownContent || markdownContent.trim().length < 100) {
  throw new Error('Claude returned empty or insufficient report content.');
}

// Build the full markdown payload with metadata header
const periodLabel = `${contextData.period_start} to ${contextData.period_end}`;

const fullMarkdown = markdownContent.trim();

return [{
  json: {
    user_id: contextData.user_id,
    client_id: contextData.client_id,
    period_start: contextData.period_start,
    period_end: contextData.period_end,
    period_label: periodLabel,
    markdown_payload: fullMarkdown,
    char_count: fullMarkdown.length,
    kpis: contextData.kpis,
    branding: contextData.branding
  }
}];

